  <p>
    <strong>SHAP values</strong> surface the top 3 risk drivers per employee — tenure, pay band vs. market, manager change frequency — displayed directly in the Power BI dashboard so an HR business partner sees not just a risk score but a recommended conversation starter.
  </p>

  <h3>Power BI engineered like code (PBIP + BPA + CI)</h3>
  <p>
    This is the part most BI projects skip. The Power BI file lives in Git as a <strong>PBIP</strong> (Power BI Project) — human-readable JSON, diffable, reviewable. A GitHub Actions workflow runs <strong>Best Practice Analyzer</strong> on every PR, failing the build if any DAX measure violates performance rules (cardinality issues, non-filtered CALCULATE patterns, missing variable declarations). The dbt test suite gates the BigQuery refresh — if any model test fails, the semantic layer does not update and the dashboard surfaces a data-quality warning instead of incorrect KPIs.
  </p>

